    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="947"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d947">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611b.9417/242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donovan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-24T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Trade Commissioner at Manila reports heavy increase in arrivals at Philippine
                    ports of Japanese cotton textiles transshipped from Hong Kong. Please report by
                    naval radio declared exports of these products for May, June, and July to date,
                    together with available information explaining increases, if any.</p>
                <p>Please forward Trade Commissioner at Manila report of declared exports of
                    Japanese cotton textiles for months of 1936 and 1937 to date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
